# Hera Motion API

Use this rule when working with Hera API integrations or when writing prompts for Hera-rendered motion graphics.

Core guidance:

- Base URL is `https://api.hera.video/v1`.
- Auth header is `x-api-key`, not `Authorization: Bearer`.
- Submit with `POST /videos`, poll with `GET /videos/{video_id}`.
- Status enum is exactly `in-progress | success | failed`.
- Download URLs live at `outputs[i].file_url`.
- Always send `outputs[]`, and `fps` must be a string such as `"30"`.
- Do not treat `failed` as transient without inspecting `outputs[i].error`.

Prompting rules:

- Use explicit bracketed timing tags: `[from <START>s to <END>s] <action>`.
- Cover the clip contiguously from `0s` to `duration_seconds`, allowing only short `0.10s` to `0.30s` overlaps for transitions.
- Derive timings from TTS transcript alignment, not from script estimates.
- Prefer deterministic slide chunking around 80 characters, with punctuation breaks once at least 30 characters have accumulated and whitespace breaks otherwise.
- Pick the visual primitive that matches the content:
- number to count-up
- comparison to bar chart
- trend to line chart
- hero phrase to kinetic text
- qualifier to callout box

Title intro pattern:

- A 4-second title card on `#F9FAFB`.
- `JetBrains Mono` title text, centered, around `96px`.
- A blinking `#06B6D4` cursor with typewriter cadence.
- Optional matching typewriter sound via ElevenLabs `/v1/sound-generation`.

Avoid decorative imagery, gradients, emoji, lens-flare effects, and vague animation language. Specify timings, coordinates, colors, font sizes, easing, and fade durations mechanically.
